To obtain a GitHub access token, follow these steps:
Log into your GitHub account and go to Settings.
In the left sidebar, click "Developer settings" and then "Personal access tokens". 
Click "Generate new token" and provide a descriptive note for the token. 
3

Select the desired scopes or permissions for the token. For pushing changes, you'll need to select the "repo" scope. 
Click "Generate token". 
3

Copy the generated token and store it securely, as it will only be shown once. 
3
Use this personal access token as your password when prompted for authentication by Git, instead of your regular GitHub account password. 
3
The key steps are navigating to the Personal Access Tokens section in your GitHub settings, generating a new token with the appropriate scopes, copying the token, and using it as your Git password when pushing changes or accessing GitHub repositories. 
3
